1
00:00:26,375 --> 00:00:28,333
[GRATEFUL KING]
You're kiddin' me.

2
00:00:28,416 --> 00:00:29,791
Even though you
announced you would

3
00:00:29,875 --> 00:00:32,166
write a new song for
the band, you haven't?

4
00:00:32,250 --> 00:00:35,666
Not a note or a measure?
Not even a single lyric?

5
00:00:35,750 --> 00:00:36,833
There's nothin'?

6
00:00:36,916 --> 00:00:41,000
There's nada?!
Diddly squat, is that it?

7
00:00:41,083 --> 00:00:43,583
Jeez, you really didn't
have to go that far.

8
00:00:43,666 --> 00:00:44,583
Oh, meow.

9
00:00:44,666 --> 00:00:46,500
But I'm right, aren't I?

10
00:00:48,041 --> 00:00:50,000
So, what do you
want from me, then?

11
00:00:50,083 --> 00:00:51,333
Huh?

12
00:00:51,416 --> 00:00:53,250
Did you think I could
do somethin' to help you?

13
00:00:53,333 --> 00:00:55,000
Actually...

14
00:00:56,125 --> 00:00:57,458
Maybe I...

15
00:00:57,541 --> 00:00:58,958
Yes.

16
00:00:59,041 --> 00:01:01,166
'Cause, you see,
I found out the reason

17
00:01:01,250 --> 00:01:04,750
I was called back here was to
prevent the Queen of Darkness

18
00:01:04,833 --> 00:01:07,833
from totally destroying
Midi City in the future.

19
00:01:07,916 --> 00:01:10,000
Oh, yeah. I know that.

20
00:01:10,083 --> 00:01:12,625
I also know that
Dagger came back.

21
00:01:12,708 --> 00:01:15,000
And now, we're supposed
to play in a battle

22
00:01:15,083 --> 00:01:19,083
of the bands soon, and it's
his band we're battling.

23
00:01:19,166 --> 00:01:21,333
But, I...

24
00:01:21,416 --> 00:01:25,875
I can't come up with
anything new at all!

25
00:01:25,958 --> 00:01:27,375
How do I do it?

26
00:01:27,458 --> 00:01:29,833
We have to beat
the Queen of Darkness

27
00:01:29,916 --> 00:01:31,708
and I just don't think
I can write a song

28
00:01:31,791 --> 00:01:35,041
that's strong enough
to win this battle for us!

29
00:01:36,583 --> 00:01:38,291
All right, kid.

30
00:01:40,125 --> 00:01:41,166
Does that mean you're
gonna help me

31
00:01:41,250 --> 00:01:43,500
with the songwriting, maybe?

32
00:01:43,583 --> 00:01:45,291
Not exactly.

33
00:01:45,375 --> 00:01:47,541
[CYAN]
Oh, I'm sorry.

34
00:01:47,625 --> 00:01:49,083
Ya gotta understand somethin'.

35
00:01:49,166 --> 00:01:51,958
There's nobody else that can
write your songs for ya.

36
00:01:52,041 --> 00:01:53,291
But don't worry.

37
00:01:53,375 --> 00:01:55,416
I think I might be able
to give you a little push

38
00:01:55,500 --> 00:01:56,833
in the right direction.

39
00:01:56,916 --> 00:01:58,416
What kind of push?

40
00:01:58,500 --> 00:01:59,791
[GRATEFUL KING]
Well, if I put it in in

41
00:01:59,875 --> 00:02:02,125
the easiest terms,
some trainin'.

42
00:02:02,208 --> 00:02:04,500
Special training.
Can you dig it?

43
00:02:04,583 --> 00:02:06,208
I guess so.

44
00:02:08,125 --> 00:02:08,791
[GRATEFUL KING]
Chop, chop!

45
00:02:08,875 --> 00:02:10,458
[CYAN whines]

46
00:02:15,625 --> 00:02:16,583
Well, kid?

47
00:02:16,666 --> 00:02:18,416
You gonna do it?
Or should I just--?

48
00:02:18,500 --> 00:02:20,166
Yeah, I'm in!

49
00:02:20,250 --> 00:02:21,291
[GRATEFUL KING]
Good.

50
00:02:21,375 --> 00:02:22,916
Then the first order
of business is...

51
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:24,333
Tell me.

52
00:02:25,458 --> 00:02:27,083
I need a massage, stat!

53
00:02:27,166 --> 00:02:28,458
Huh?

54
00:02:29,791 --> 00:02:30,750
Listen!

55
00:02:30,833 --> 00:02:32,458
This is part of
your training, too!

56
00:02:32,541 --> 00:02:34,541
Well, if you say so.

57
00:02:37,041 --> 00:02:39,291
[GRATEFUL KING] Hey, you're not
just kneadin' dough here.

58
00:02:39,375 --> 00:02:41,291
Lemme hear the snap
of your wrists.

59
00:02:41,375 --> 00:02:43,083
I wanna feel some rhythm!

60
00:02:43,166 --> 00:02:44,958
Yes, sir!

61
00:02:46,333 --> 00:02:48,000
[GRATEFUL KING] By the way,
did you tell the other girls

62
00:02:48,083 --> 00:02:50,000
in Plasmagica about this?

63
00:02:50,083 --> 00:02:51,500
Uh.

64
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:56,041
I knew they'd just be worried
if I said anything to them.

65
00:02:56,125 --> 00:02:58,958
So I left without a word.

66
00:02:59,041 --> 00:03:00,833
Ah, got it.

67
00:03:04,541 --> 00:03:06,083
[GRATEFUL KING]
Hey, it's not break time!

68
00:03:06,166 --> 00:03:07,541
Oh, right!

69
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:12,958
♪

70
00:03:17,166 --> 00:03:20,125
[PLASMAGICA]
♪ Go! Go! Go! Go! Go! Go! ♪

71
00:03:20,208 --> 00:03:21,458
♪ Pumping Jumping! ♪

72
00:03:21,541 --> 00:03:24,541
♪ Go! Go! Go! Go! Go! Go! ♪

73
00:03:24,625 --> 00:03:25,958
♪ Jump to the beat! Hey! ♪

74
00:03:26,041 --> 00:03:28,125
[CYAN] ♪ Dontcha come at me
with your monotone ♪

75
00:03:28,208 --> 00:03:30,333
♪ Feelin' somethin'
more harmonious ♪

76
00:03:30,416 --> 00:03:31,833
[CHUCHU]
♪ Waiting, to take a breath ♪

77
00:03:31,916 --> 00:03:34,375
♪ I look, listen,
oh so carefully ♪

78
00:03:34,458 --> 00:03:36,750
[RETOREE] ♪ Oh baby,
can you hear the chords ♪

79
00:03:36,833 --> 00:03:39,041
♪ Soundin' sweet the more
we rock the pop ♪

80
00:03:39,125 --> 00:03:40,958
[MOA] ♪ Let's mix and
match our swing now ♪

81
00:03:41,041 --> 00:03:44,041
♪ To make the music that we've
all been feelin' inside ♪

82
00:03:44,125 --> 00:03:47,375
[CYAN, CHUCHU] ♪ (Passhuwa!
Pappasshuwa! Pashuwa, yes!) ♪

83
00:03:47,458 --> 00:03:49,083
[CYAN]
♪ 'Cause even in my dreams ♪

84
00:03:49,166 --> 00:03:51,833
♪ I hear the sound
of your voice ♪

85
00:03:51,916 --> 00:03:55,791
[CHUCHU] ♪ In you I finally see
There is no other choice ♪

86
00:03:55,875 --> 00:03:58,333
[RETOREE] ♪ I know I can
keep pushing ahead ♪

87
00:03:58,416 --> 00:04:00,291
♪ And that I can really change ♪

88
00:04:00,375 --> 00:04:02,958
[MOA] ♪ All I need is
to find melodies ♪

89
00:04:03,041 --> 00:04:04,666
♪ I haven't
discovered just yet ♪

90
00:04:04,750 --> 00:04:07,208
[CYAN, CHUCHU] ♪ Everybody Rock!
Rock! Give it your all! ♪

91
00:04:07,291 --> 00:04:08,958
♪ Just sing and be yourself! ♪

92
00:04:09,041 --> 00:04:10,708
♪ Keep on keepin' on
and on and on and on ♪

93
00:04:10,791 --> 00:04:13,500
♪ and cramming emotions
into your music ♪

94
00:04:13,583 --> 00:04:16,041
♪ Everybody Rock! Rock!
With all your heart! ♪

95
00:04:16,125 --> 00:04:18,250
♪ And soon you'll
hear new melodies ♪

96
00:04:18,333 --> 00:04:19,166
♪ Hear the pulsing beat ♪

97
00:04:19,250 --> 00:04:20,708
♪ The power of the rhythm ♪

98
00:04:20,791 --> 00:04:22,375
♪ The magic never stops ♪

99
00:04:22,458 --> 00:04:25,125
[PLASMAGICA] ♪ All you need is
harmony (words don't matter) ♪

100
00:04:25,208 --> 00:04:27,250
♪ Honesty
(With your feelings) ♪

101
00:04:27,333 --> 00:04:29,875
♪ Keep on strumming! Keep on
going! Keep on and on! ♪

102
00:04:29,958 --> 00:04:32,791
♪ Go! Go! Go! Go! Go! Go! ♪

103
00:04:32,875 --> 00:04:34,416
♪ Jump to the beat! Hey! ♪

104
00:04:42,583 --> 00:04:43,833
[ROM]
All right, stop!

105
00:04:43,916 --> 00:04:45,083
Come on, you guys!

106
00:04:45,166 --> 00:04:47,875
We aren't playing
in sync at all here!

107
00:04:47,958 --> 00:04:49,416
Uh, you sure, man?

108
00:04:49,500 --> 00:04:50,833
We're never gonna
get revenge on those

109
00:04:50,916 --> 00:04:53,666
flashy fools if we
keep playin' like crap!

110
00:04:55,375 --> 00:04:56,666
Well.

111
00:04:56,750 --> 00:04:58,458
[growls]

112
00:04:58,541 --> 00:05:01,416
[ROM] I have no choice.
So I'll do it again.

113
00:05:01,500 --> 00:05:04,333
It's time to get you
guys psyched up, now!

114
00:05:04,416 --> 00:05:07,208
Wait, Rom, please not
in the face, okay?

115
00:05:07,291 --> 00:05:08,208
So listen!

116
00:05:08,291 --> 00:05:10,333
We're goin' back
to training camp!

117
00:05:10,416 --> 00:05:12,458
[ALL]
Huh?

118
00:05:12,541 --> 00:05:13,791
Yo, Rom!

119
00:05:13,875 --> 00:05:16,166
I know we must've passed
this place earlier, right?

120
00:05:16,250 --> 00:05:17,916
[AION]
We've gone astray in Helheim,

121
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:20,666
drowned by the inky
darkness of Hades.

122
00:05:20,750 --> 00:05:22,041
At this snail's pace,

123
00:05:22,125 --> 00:05:24,541
it will be nightfall
before we arrive there.

124
00:05:24,625 --> 00:05:25,833
Hence.

125
00:05:25,916 --> 00:05:27,375
Shut up, you octopus!

126
00:05:27,458 --> 00:05:30,166
Blame this stupid map
the old man drew for us!

127
00:05:34,250 --> 00:05:35,875
[YAIBA]
Oh, hence.

128
00:05:35,958 --> 00:05:39,500
Aw, damn it! I'm starving!

129
00:05:48,041 --> 00:05:50,250
[UCHURA] Hey, Kintaurus,
this guard duty gig

130
00:05:50,333 --> 00:05:52,375
is pretty easy!

131
00:05:52,458 --> 00:05:54,541
You're not kidding, Uchura.

132
00:05:54,625 --> 00:05:57,916
If I'd known before, Maybe I
would have practiced a little!

133
00:05:58,000 --> 00:06:00,625
[chuckles] How
dedicated, Leader.

134
00:06:00,708 --> 00:06:04,208
But, anyway, they sure
told us we were guards,

135
00:06:04,291 --> 00:06:06,250
but what are we
actually guarding?

136
00:06:06,333 --> 00:06:08,500
[KINTAURUS] Well, I heard
that somewhere in the ruins

137
00:06:08,583 --> 00:06:10,333
on the other side
of this forest,

138
00:06:10,416 --> 00:06:13,416
there's an unbelievably
huge Melodisian stone.

139
00:06:13,500 --> 00:06:14,791
[UCHURA]
Whoa, no way.

140
00:06:14,875 --> 00:06:16,708
But, no matter what happens,

141
00:06:16,791 --> 00:06:20,083
as long as we have
Daishizen, I'm not worried.

142
00:06:20,166 --> 00:06:21,666
[KINTAURUS, UCHURA, DEYAN gasp]

143
00:06:21,750 --> 00:06:23,291
Hey, someone's coming!

144
00:06:24,833 --> 00:06:26,958
Aw, man. Finally, we made it.

145
00:06:27,041 --> 00:06:28,875
That took forever.

146
00:06:28,958 --> 00:06:29,958
Huh?

147
00:06:30,041 --> 00:06:31,708
[KINTAURUS]
Uh, hey, trespassers!

148
00:06:31,791 --> 00:06:34,750
You won't get one
single step p-past us...

149
00:06:34,833 --> 00:06:35,708
I think.

150
00:06:35,791 --> 00:06:37,166
What did you say?

151
00:06:37,250 --> 00:06:38,583
Who the hell are you guys?

152
00:06:38,666 --> 00:06:40,875
We-We all guard this place!

153
00:06:40,958 --> 00:06:42,208
[CROW]
You're kidding, right?

154
00:06:42,291 --> 00:06:43,708
You heard me!

155
00:06:43,791 --> 00:06:46,125
We can't let you guys in here.
You'll have to turn back!

156
00:06:46,208 --> 00:06:47,208
Huh?

157
00:06:47,291 --> 00:06:49,333
Rom, what do we do now?

158
00:06:49,416 --> 00:06:50,500
We have important business

159
00:06:50,583 --> 00:06:52,041
on the other side
of that gate, man.

160
00:06:52,125 --> 00:06:55,041
You'll have to let us through.

161
00:06:55,125 --> 00:06:57,875
Don't come any closer!
You will regret it!

162
00:06:57,958 --> 00:06:59,333
Yeah?

163
00:06:59,416 --> 00:07:01,708
I could say the same for you.

164
00:07:02,458 --> 00:07:05,791
[UCHURA]
Daishizen, 'get em. Please!

165
00:07:05,875 --> 00:07:09,583
[DAISHIZEN]
It will be done.

166
00:07:11,041 --> 00:07:12,833
The hell?

167
00:07:12,916 --> 00:07:15,375
[DAISHIZEN]
Now, be gone!

168
00:07:15,458 --> 00:07:17,083
No. What's happening?

169
00:07:17,166 --> 00:07:20,208
The mountain!
It's coming towards us!

170
00:07:21,583 --> 00:07:23,458
[ALL screaming]

171
00:07:28,458 --> 00:07:31,416
ALL scream]

172
00:07:32,458 --> 00:07:34,500
[UCHURA] Daishizen doesn't
mess around, does he?

173
00:07:34,583 --> 00:07:36,500
He might've gone
a little bit overboard.

174
00:07:36,583 --> 00:07:38,500
Who cares, he got
rid of them, right?

175
00:07:38,583 --> 00:07:39,708
It's all good.

176
00:07:46,958 --> 00:07:49,250
Hey, you guys!
Are you all right?

177
00:07:49,333 --> 00:07:51,250
Oh, crap. I'm slippin', man.

178
00:07:51,333 --> 00:07:52,583
I'm gonna fall.

179
00:07:52,666 --> 00:07:55,833
And thus, it would seem
we must prepare ourselves.

180
00:07:55,916 --> 00:07:57,166
So hence--

181
00:07:58,625 --> 00:08:01,416
C'mon, wussies!
Don't give up on me!

182
00:08:02,791 --> 00:08:05,666
I refuse to die,
not here, not now!

183
00:08:05,750 --> 00:08:08,375
I won't accept that reality!

184
00:08:10,333 --> 00:08:11,958
[gasps]

185
00:08:12,041 --> 00:08:13,166
[ALL gasp]

186
00:08:14,916 --> 00:08:16,041
Huh?

187
00:08:16,125 --> 00:08:17,875
You whippersnappers
were takin' too long,

188
00:08:17,958 --> 00:08:20,791
so I figgered I'd come
and fetch ya. Heh, heh!

189
00:08:20,875 --> 00:08:22,375
[ROM]
Old man!

190
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:27,375
[ALL laugh]

191
00:08:29,375 --> 00:08:35,750
[ALL chattering]

192
00:08:35,833 --> 00:08:39,375
[laughing]

193
00:08:48,875 --> 00:08:50,250
[AION gasps]

194
00:08:52,166 --> 00:08:53,375
[clears throat]

195
00:08:55,041 --> 00:08:56,166
[YAIBA]
Rom.

196
00:08:59,541 --> 00:09:02,083
[gasps] Where'd you find this?

197
00:09:02,166 --> 00:09:05,041
[YAIBA] It was buried in
the archives at the agency.

198
00:09:08,250 --> 00:09:09,625
Oh, man.

199
00:09:11,083 --> 00:09:12,666
[ROM]
Crazy.

200
00:09:12,750 --> 00:09:15,291
This is the last song
of the band I was in once.

201
00:09:15,375 --> 00:09:16,541
A long time ago.

202
00:09:16,625 --> 00:09:18,583
The last?

203
00:09:18,666 --> 00:09:23,541
[FANS cheering]

204
00:09:23,625 --> 00:09:25,541
[inhales, exhales]

205
00:09:25,625 --> 00:09:28,166
[panting]

206
00:09:28,250 --> 00:09:29,458
No dreams are real.

207
00:09:29,541 --> 00:09:31,750
They're just illusions.

208
00:09:35,750 --> 00:09:37,458
[ROM]
Some time ago,

209
00:09:37,541 --> 00:09:40,291
I was in a band with this guy.

210
00:09:40,375 --> 00:09:44,500
See, way back in those days,
all I needed to be happy

211
00:09:44,583 --> 00:09:48,041
was to play as much
music as possible.

212
00:09:48,125 --> 00:09:50,875
We were always goin' all out.

213
00:09:50,958 --> 00:09:53,166
We weren't scared of anything,

214
00:09:53,250 --> 00:09:56,041
and we really thought
we were headin' to the top.

215
00:09:56,125 --> 00:09:59,541
But, I didn't
realize at the time...

216
00:09:59,625 --> 00:10:01,625
Shu's goals for
the band changed,

217
00:10:01,708 --> 00:10:05,125
and he didn't bother
to let me in on that.

218
00:10:05,208 --> 00:10:08,500
I guess he was focused on
a place too far in the future,

219
00:10:08,583 --> 00:10:11,041
right from the start.

220
00:10:11,125 --> 00:10:13,791
So, we decided it
was best to break up

221
00:10:13,875 --> 00:10:17,791
and not too long after that,
we both went our separate ways.

222
00:10:17,875 --> 00:10:20,666
So, then, are you--

223
00:10:20,750 --> 00:10:22,916
Nah, the past is the past.

224
00:10:24,916 --> 00:10:26,958
[ROM]
Okay, it's gettin' late.

225
00:10:27,041 --> 00:10:29,416
Big day tomorrow, we've
got intense rehearsal!

226
00:10:29,500 --> 00:10:31,291
So be ready for it, boys!

227
00:10:31,375 --> 00:10:33,541
Uh, right.

228
00:10:35,875 --> 00:10:38,250
[YAIBA] Do you suppose he's
going to be all right?

229
00:10:38,333 --> 00:10:40,166
[AION] The fierce wind that
blew through the hollow

230
00:10:40,250 --> 00:10:43,000
of Rom's regrets should
have calmed by now.

231
00:10:43,083 --> 00:10:44,583
[YAIBA]
Yes, but--

232
00:10:44,666 --> 00:10:45,916
[CROW]
Hm.

233
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:47,708
Crow?

234
00:10:48,916 --> 00:10:50,875
I think I have an idea.

235
00:11:09,291 --> 00:11:10,375
Man, I'm impressed.

236
00:11:10,458 --> 00:11:13,208
The old guy's got
some real nice gear.

237
00:11:13,291 --> 00:11:16,416
But, meanwhile, why the hell
aren't my bandmates here yet?

238
00:11:16,500 --> 00:11:19,208
If they tell me they overslept,
I'm gonna put the hurt on 'em.

239
00:11:19,291 --> 00:11:21,750
[CROW] We're here! You
haven't been waiting long,

240
00:11:21,833 --> 00:11:22,833
have ya?

241
00:11:22,916 --> 00:11:24,666
[ROM]
Not cool! You are late again!

242
00:11:24,750 --> 00:11:27,000
The rehearsals we have at
training camp are too valuable

243
00:11:27,083 --> 00:11:28,416
for you to waste your
time being so selfish.

244
00:11:28,500 --> 00:11:29,791
[CROW]
Check it out.

245
00:11:29,875 --> 00:11:32,000
We stayed up all night
writing this brand new song.

246
00:11:32,083 --> 00:11:33,166
That's why we're late.

247
00:11:33,250 --> 00:11:35,625
Huh? Lemme see that.

248
00:11:37,125 --> 00:11:38,541
Yaiba and I wrote it
with my bright,

249
00:11:38,625 --> 00:11:41,041
fervent spirit of the
Apocalypse burning crimson,

250
00:11:41,125 --> 00:11:43,458
and Aion put his whole
dark soul into it as well.

251
00:11:43,541 --> 00:11:45,458
It's full of passion, man!

252
00:11:46,541 --> 00:11:51,291
[gasps] So you're saying
you spent time on it?

253
00:11:51,375 --> 00:11:53,833
[CROW] Damn skippy! We didn't
even sleep last night.

254
00:11:53,916 --> 00:11:55,083
[CROW laughs]

255
00:12:01,708 --> 00:12:03,375
Hey, Rom. We just wanted--

256
00:12:03,458 --> 00:12:04,416
Don't say it!

257
00:12:04,500 --> 00:12:05,791
[ALL gasp]

258
00:12:15,708 --> 00:12:17,125
[GRATEFUL KING]
Hey, Cyan!

259
00:12:17,208 --> 00:12:18,625
[CYAN]
Yes?

260
00:12:18,708 --> 00:12:19,958
[GRATEFUL KING] Bring these
guests' bags to their rooms,

261
00:12:20,041 --> 00:12:22,750
and stat! Make sure you
get the right ones, 'kay?

262
00:12:22,833 --> 00:12:24,958
Huh? By myself?

263
00:12:25,041 --> 00:12:25,958
[GRATEFUL KING]
Of course.

264
00:12:26,041 --> 00:12:28,208
It's part of the
special training.

265
00:12:33,125 --> 00:12:35,208
[grunting]

266
00:12:39,291 --> 00:12:40,916
[CYAN]
I'm so tired.

267
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:42,000
[GRATEFUL KING]
Yo, Cyan!

268
00:12:42,083 --> 00:12:43,750
Uh, yeah?

269
00:12:45,041 --> 00:12:46,500
Go put those big blocks of ice

270
00:12:46,583 --> 00:12:49,666
in the freezer before
they turn into puddles.

271
00:12:49,750 --> 00:12:52,041
All four of them.

272
00:12:52,125 --> 00:12:53,791
But how will they
all fit inside?

273
00:12:53,875 --> 00:12:54,833
They're too big!

274
00:12:54,916 --> 00:12:55,875
Well,

275
00:12:55,958 --> 00:12:58,166
that's why you
gotta cut em' down.

276
00:12:58,250 --> 00:13:01,458
Better hurry up. The sun
is pretty brutal today.

277
00:13:01,541 --> 00:13:02,791
Huh?!

278
00:13:05,666 --> 00:13:07,375
Melting, melting.

279
00:13:13,375 --> 00:13:15,375
Next, I need you
to clean the pool.

280
00:13:15,458 --> 00:13:17,916
And it's big, so you
gotta be thorough.

281
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:21,750
Really? All this by myself, too?

282
00:13:21,833 --> 00:13:24,125
[GRATEFUL KING] Do you wanna
write a hit song, or not?

283
00:13:24,208 --> 00:13:25,541
[CYAN whimpers]

284
00:13:28,041 --> 00:13:30,875
None of these things are
related to songwriting.

285
00:13:30,958 --> 00:13:34,125
I don't get how any of them are
supposed to help me with it.

286
00:13:34,208 --> 00:13:35,333
[GRATEFUL KING]
Hey, Cyan!

287
00:13:35,416 --> 00:13:37,208
Uh, yeah?

288
00:13:37,291 --> 00:13:39,458
[yelps]

289
00:13:48,250 --> 00:13:50,291
[CHUCHU] Ever since I first
heard the sugary sound

290
00:13:50,375 --> 00:13:52,166
of your beautiful voice,

291
00:13:52,250 --> 00:13:55,208
I decided we'd make
a terrific team.

292
00:13:55,291 --> 00:13:56,416
I dunno.

293
00:13:56,500 --> 00:13:58,958
I'm not great
singing to a crowd.

294
00:13:59,041 --> 00:14:01,000
I think you'll rock it.

295
00:14:01,083 --> 00:14:03,541
[MOA]
Yeah, I do, too, pyuru!

296
00:14:03,625 --> 00:14:05,791
[CYAN]
I love you guys!

297
00:14:08,750 --> 00:14:10,041
Miss you.

298
00:14:11,500 --> 00:14:14,375
[GRATEFUL KING]
You throwin' in the towel?

299
00:14:14,458 --> 00:14:16,000
[CYAN]
Oh. No, I'm not.

300
00:14:16,083 --> 00:14:19,375
But I was wondering--
how my doing all these

301
00:14:19,458 --> 00:14:22,750
crazy chores is somehow gonna
help me write a good song.

302
00:14:22,833 --> 00:14:26,083
Well, kid, it depends on you.

303
00:14:26,166 --> 00:14:29,250
What do you mean by that?

304
00:14:29,333 --> 00:14:32,000
[DARUDAYU] Every living
creature in this entire world,

305
00:14:32,083 --> 00:14:35,833
is governed by the power
of Melodisian Stones.

306
00:14:35,916 --> 00:14:37,625
The source of that great power

307
00:14:37,708 --> 00:14:40,875
is rumored to be the
phantom Melodisian Almaz.

308
00:14:40,958 --> 00:14:43,791
However, this is not something
that is easily obtained,

309
00:14:43,875 --> 00:14:44,833
is it, girls?

310
00:14:44,916 --> 00:14:46,291
No.

311
00:14:46,375 --> 00:14:49,083
But, dear Master, I believe
that being on this journey

312
00:14:49,166 --> 00:14:50,958
means we've already
been training.

313
00:14:51,041 --> 00:14:53,083
The more difficulties
we encounter,

314
00:14:53,166 --> 00:14:56,583
the more satisfaction we will
feel when we finally obtain it.

315
00:14:56,666 --> 00:15:02,291
[DARUDAYU chuckles]
Oh, my!

316
00:15:02,375 --> 00:15:04,166
Both of you have shown
tremendous growth

317
00:15:04,250 --> 00:15:05,500
while with me!

318
00:15:05,583 --> 00:15:08,041
Which will render our
victory that much sweeter.

319
00:15:08,125 --> 00:15:10,291
And now, let us go!

320
00:15:10,375 --> 00:15:11,958
[A, UN]
Yes!

321
00:15:12,041 --> 00:15:15,541
[UCHURA sighs] Suddenly,
I'm feeling so tired, man.

322
00:15:15,625 --> 00:15:16,958
Yeah, me, too.

323
00:15:17,041 --> 00:15:21,083
I mean, I thought this part-time
job was gonna be easy.

324
00:15:21,166 --> 00:15:23,500
By the way, Leader,
I've been trying to find

325
00:15:23,583 --> 00:15:25,666
a good way to tell you this.

326
00:15:25,750 --> 00:15:28,833
That t-shirt is
utterly ridiculous.

327
00:15:28,916 --> 00:15:32,750
Huh? Fine, so don't
wear it then, Deyan.

328
00:15:32,833 --> 00:15:35,458
Hey, Uchura. My shirt's
not lame, is it?

329
00:15:35,541 --> 00:15:37,041
[UCHURA]
U-Uh...

330
00:15:37,125 --> 00:15:38,333
[KINTAURUS]
Come on.

331
00:15:38,416 --> 00:15:41,416
[DAISHIZEN]
Someone has arrived.

332
00:15:41,500 --> 00:15:42,833
[KINTAURUS]
Who do you think it is?

333
00:15:42,916 --> 00:15:45,666
Maybe those guys from
earlier came back?

334
00:15:55,041 --> 00:15:56,208
What?

335
00:15:56,291 --> 00:15:59,625
Could it be Tsurezurenaru
Ayatsuri Mugenan?

336
00:15:59,708 --> 00:16:01,875
[UCHURA]
Their aura is really powerful!

337
00:16:01,958 --> 00:16:03,791
What are they even doing here?

338
00:16:03,875 --> 00:16:06,750
[DARUDAYU] We have reasons
to enter this fortress

339
00:16:06,833 --> 00:16:09,416
which are far beyond your
capacity to understand.

340
00:16:09,500 --> 00:16:11,583
Please be good
enough let us pass.

341
00:16:11,666 --> 00:16:12,833
What are we gonna do?

342
00:16:12,916 --> 00:16:14,708
[UCHURA]
I mean, it's Tsurezure!

343
00:16:14,791 --> 00:16:17,041
But we still have
to do our jobs.

344
00:16:17,125 --> 00:16:19,458
Um, let's see. Uh...

345
00:16:19,541 --> 00:16:22,125
"As the area beyond
is a place of holiness,

346
00:16:22,208 --> 00:16:24,666
only those deemed truly
worthy are granted access

347
00:16:24,750 --> 00:16:26,916
beyond its hallowed gates."

348
00:16:27,000 --> 00:16:28,916
So. Yeah, that.

349
00:16:29,000 --> 00:16:30,166
Oh?

350
00:16:30,250 --> 00:16:32,541
Well, if that's really
the case then, please,

351
00:16:32,625 --> 00:16:36,333
ascertain carefully with
those keen eyes of yours.

352
00:16:36,416 --> 00:16:39,291
You will decide soon enough
how truly worthy we are!

353
00:16:39,375 --> 00:16:40,625
[TSUREZURENARU AYATSURI MUGENAN]
♪ Fluttering away ♪

354
00:16:40,708 --> 00:16:42,166
♪ Flowers swing and sway ♪

355
00:16:42,250 --> 00:16:44,750
♪ With thousands of paper
lanterns shaking in the night ♪

356
00:16:44,833 --> 00:16:49,666
♪ When this drunken evening
and festivities are done ♪

357
00:16:49,750 --> 00:16:51,333
♪ Will you open up your eyes ♪

358
00:16:51,416 --> 00:16:52,875
♪ And see the morning light? ♪

359
00:16:52,958 --> 00:16:55,583
♪ Here comes the beating
of erratic demon drums ♪

360
00:16:55,666 --> 00:16:57,250
♪ For tonight we
will will basque ♪

361
00:16:57,333 --> 00:16:58,625
♪ in the beauty of the moon ♪

362
00:16:58,708 --> 00:17:01,625
♪ As the sixteenth night
fades into the dawn ♪

363
00:17:01,708 --> 00:17:03,708
♪ Until the sun
comes up we'll keep ♪

364
00:17:03,791 --> 00:17:07,291
♪ Dancing on ♪

365
00:17:07,375 --> 00:17:12,333
♪

366
00:17:20,791 --> 00:17:23,458
[UCHURA] Tsurezure are
so amazing, aren't they?

367
00:17:23,541 --> 00:17:26,583
Oh yes. They must pass
without question.

368
00:17:26,666 --> 00:17:30,041
Yeah. There's no
reason to refuse them.

369
00:17:30,125 --> 00:17:32,875
[DAISHIZEN]
Open the gates!

370
00:17:40,000 --> 00:17:41,541
Ah.

371
00:17:42,583 --> 00:17:44,250
[DARUDAYU]
I am quite certain.

372
00:17:44,333 --> 00:17:48,166
Our hope lies waiting for us on
the other side of this light.

373
00:17:48,250 --> 00:17:49,833
A! And, Un!

374
00:17:49,916 --> 00:17:52,333
It is time to go through!

375
00:17:52,416 --> 00:17:53,666
[A, UN]
Yes!

376
00:17:57,291 --> 00:18:00,000
[GRATEFUL KING]
Last leg of your trainin' tour.

377
00:18:00,083 --> 00:18:02,333
[CYAN]
What do I have to do now?

378
00:18:02,416 --> 00:18:04,291
You gotta play some music.

379
00:18:04,375 --> 00:18:06,291
[CYAN]
Huh? Wow, finally?

380
00:18:06,375 --> 00:18:09,041
Oh, yay!

381
00:18:09,125 --> 00:18:12,166
Cool! There's a studio here!

382
00:18:12,250 --> 00:18:13,375
[GRATEFUL KING]
That's right.

383
00:18:13,458 --> 00:18:15,916
This means I'm ready
to write my song now!

384
00:18:16,000 --> 00:18:18,291
You're gonna be helping
me with that, right?

385
00:18:18,375 --> 00:18:20,166
Not a chance, kid.

386
00:18:20,250 --> 00:18:21,125
Then...

387
00:18:21,208 --> 00:18:23,125
What am I supposed to--

388
00:18:23,208 --> 00:18:25,083
[GRATEFUL KING] I want you to
play all of those instruments

389
00:18:25,166 --> 00:18:27,541
you see in front of you.

390
00:18:27,625 --> 00:18:28,875
But, I--

391
00:18:28,958 --> 00:18:30,125
[GRATEFUL KING] When you
can play the two guitars,

392
00:18:30,208 --> 00:18:31,916
the bass, and the drums
all at the same time,

393
00:18:32,000 --> 00:18:33,625
then give me a jingle.

394
00:18:33,708 --> 00:18:34,791
See ya later, sister.

395
00:18:34,875 --> 00:18:37,416
What?! But there's
no way I can do that!

396
00:18:37,500 --> 00:18:39,666
Wait, Mr. Grateful King!

397
00:18:41,625 --> 00:18:44,208
So it looks like you're
a quitter after all.

398
00:18:44,291 --> 00:18:46,375
With a rotten
attitude like that,

399
00:18:46,458 --> 00:18:49,541
you're never gonna
find the god of music.

400
00:18:49,625 --> 00:18:52,791
The god of music?
What do you mean?

401
00:18:52,875 --> 00:18:56,708
You of all people should know.
Unless you meet this god,

402
00:18:56,791 --> 00:19:00,458
then you can kiss writin'
any amazing songs goodbye.

403
00:19:12,708 --> 00:19:16,666
Impossible. There's no
way I can do it.

404
00:19:16,750 --> 00:19:20,375
Why's he making such
unreasonable demands?

405
00:19:20,458 --> 00:19:23,500
Stupid Grateful King.

406
00:19:26,583 --> 00:19:31,291
[guitar plays]

407
00:19:33,500 --> 00:19:34,291
[CHUCHU]
Cyan!

408
00:19:34,375 --> 00:19:35,750
[gasps]

409
00:19:35,833 --> 00:19:38,708
Remember, we're counting on you.

410
00:19:38,791 --> 00:19:40,625
[CYAN]

411
00:19:40,708 --> 00:19:43,375
I'm really looking forward
to the new song, pyuru!

412
00:19:43,458 --> 00:19:46,458
Cyan, are you sure
you're all right?

413
00:19:51,416 --> 00:19:53,041
[CYAN]
What am I doing?

414
00:19:53,125 --> 00:19:56,125
I'm making the
same mistake again!

415
00:19:56,208 --> 00:19:59,625
I can't believe how
stupid I've been.

416
00:19:59,708 --> 00:20:03,541
I just hope they can forgive me.

417
00:20:03,625 --> 00:20:09,291
[panting]

418
00:20:18,125 --> 00:20:23,291
Mister King, I get it. Finally.

419
00:20:23,375 --> 00:20:27,041
The god of music you
told me to go find.

420
00:20:27,125 --> 00:20:33,750
Was always, always there,
and never left my side, ever!

421
00:20:33,833 --> 00:20:39,666
[sobs]

422
00:20:39,750 --> 00:20:43,583
[phone rings]

423
00:20:43,666 --> 00:20:45,833
Retoree.

424
00:20:45,916 --> 00:20:47,416
[RETOREE]
Cyan?

425
00:20:49,708 --> 00:20:54,583
I'm sorry. I let--
I let everybody down.

426
00:20:54,666 --> 00:20:57,750
I haven't made progress
on the new song.

427
00:20:57,833 --> 00:20:59,333
But I was scared
to tell you all,

428
00:20:59,416 --> 00:21:04,083
'cause you'd be mad.
Don't hate me.

429
00:21:04,166 --> 00:21:05,291
[RETOREE]
Here.

430
00:21:12,250 --> 00:21:14,916
Oh, you're here.

431
00:21:15,000 --> 00:21:17,458
Hey, please, stop crying.

432
00:21:17,541 --> 00:21:19,875
You never needed to go
through this all by yourself.

433
00:21:19,958 --> 00:21:21,250
We're a team!

434
00:21:21,333 --> 00:21:24,458
However, we also want
to apologize to you, sugar.

435
00:21:24,541 --> 00:21:27,041
We had no idea that we
were pushing you so hard.

436
00:21:27,125 --> 00:21:30,000
Cyan, we're so sorry.

437
00:21:30,083 --> 00:21:34,000
[CYAN]
No. That's not it!

438
00:21:34,083 --> 00:21:35,708
I'm the one who's sorry.

439
00:21:35,791 --> 00:21:38,000
I abandoned all of you.

440
00:21:38,083 --> 00:21:40,833
I'm a terrible
friend and band mate!

441
00:21:40,916 --> 00:21:42,958
All is forgiven, Cyan.

442
00:21:43,041 --> 00:21:45,250
Now let's put our heads
together and write

443
00:21:45,333 --> 00:21:46,833
the best song we've ever done!

444
00:21:46,916 --> 00:21:49,166
We can do it, pyuru!

445
00:21:49,250 --> 00:21:53,375
Yeah! Thanks so much,
my friends.

446
00:21:56,500 --> 00:22:00,625
Wait a second, you guys,
how did you find me?

447
00:22:00,708 --> 00:22:02,875
We knew there was only
one person in the world

448
00:22:02,958 --> 00:22:05,833
you'd ever ask to help
you and that's him.

449
00:22:05,916 --> 00:22:07,458
So, here we are.

450
00:22:10,625 --> 00:22:14,125
[CYAN]
Mr. Grateful King, thank you!

451
00:22:17,125 --> 00:22:18,083
[PLASMAGICA]
♪ Chuchu! ♪

452
00:22:18,166 --> 00:22:19,625
[CHUCHU]
Okay, sugars. Let's do this!

453
00:22:19,708 --> 00:22:20,958
[PLASMAGICA]
♪ Cyan! ♪

454
00:22:21,041 --> 00:22:22,375
[CYAN] It's time for everyone
to hear our music!

455
00:22:22,458 --> 00:22:23,500
[PLASMAGICA]
♪ Retoree! ♪

456
00:22:23,583 --> 00:22:24,916
[RETOREE]
We're so perfectly in tune.

457
00:22:25,000 --> 00:22:25,833
[PLASMAGICA]
♪ Moa! ♪

458
00:22:25,916 --> 00:22:27,666
[MOA]
Pyuru, pyuru, pyuru...!

459
00:22:27,750 --> 00:22:30,416
[PLASMAGICA] ♪ Tell me
Why I'm so happy with you? ♪

460
00:22:30,500 --> 00:22:33,041
♪ Tell me
How we have so much fun ♪

461
00:22:33,125 --> 00:22:35,750
♪ Tell me
I know I'm ready for it ♪

462
00:22:35,833 --> 00:22:37,041
♪ Let's (Fine!) go! (Fine!) ♪

463
00:22:37,125 --> 00:22:38,291
♪ Sing for the show!
(Let's go) ♪

464
00:22:38,375 --> 00:22:41,000
♪ CHU-CHU-CHU
CHU-CHU CHU CHU-LU-LU ♪

465
00:22:41,083 --> 00:22:43,666
♪ CHU-CHU-CHU
CHU-CHU CHU CHU-LU-LU ♪

466
00:22:43,750 --> 00:22:46,291
♪ CHU-CHU-CHU
CHU-CHU CHU CHU-LU-LU ♪

467
00:22:46,375 --> 00:22:48,375
♪ CHU-LU-LU-LU ♪

468
00:22:49,500 --> 00:22:51,250
[CYAN] ♪ I feel like the
thumping of my heart ♪

469
00:22:51,333 --> 00:22:52,958
♪ is speeding up the rhythm ♪

470
00:22:53,041 --> 00:22:54,625
♪ What can I do?
(Yeah, yeah, yeah!) ♪

471
00:22:54,708 --> 00:22:56,541
[CHUCHU]
♪ My spirit is so electrified ♪

472
00:22:56,625 --> 00:23:00,083
♪ I go anywhere I want to
(Que sera sera sera) ♪

473
00:23:00,166 --> 00:23:02,166
[RETOREE] ♪ Our memories
are piling up like photos ♪

474
00:23:02,250 --> 00:23:05,041
♪ In a picture album of
melodies (Yeah, yeah, yeah!) ♪

475
00:23:05,125 --> 00:23:07,291
[MOA] ♪ When I need recharging
all I have to do ♪

476
00:23:07,375 --> 00:23:09,708
♪ Is play the album
of my memories (Yay!) ♪

477
00:23:09,791 --> 00:23:12,916
[CYAN] ♪ We'll keep writing
all these new songs ♪

478
00:23:13,000 --> 00:23:15,041
[RETOREE]
♪ Our imagination won't stop ♪

479
00:23:15,125 --> 00:23:16,333
[CYAN, CHUCHU]
♪ Almost done! ♪

480
00:23:16,416 --> 00:23:18,541
[RETOREE, MOA]
♪ (Precious number one music) ♪

481
00:23:18,625 --> 00:23:21,083
[PLASMAGICA] ♪ Now put it
all together! Yay! ♪

482
00:23:21,166 --> 00:23:23,750
♪ Tell me
How you inspire music ♪

483
00:23:23,833 --> 00:23:26,375
♪ In me?
My singing is all for you ♪

484
00:23:26,458 --> 00:23:30,458
♪ Tell me
Why I never noticed until now? ♪

485
00:23:30,541 --> 00:23:31,750
♪ (My song is you!!) ♪

486
00:23:31,833 --> 00:23:34,333
♪ I know, it's all
in my subconcious ♪

487
00:23:34,416 --> 00:23:37,041
♪ I know, you're with me
through everything ♪

488
00:23:37,125 --> 00:23:39,791
♪ I know, you're
in my heart forever ♪

489
00:23:39,875 --> 00:23:41,208
♪ Always (Fine! Fine!) ♪

490
00:23:41,291 --> 00:23:42,500
♪ I love you (Once more) ♪

491
00:23:42,583 --> 00:23:43,750
♪ Always (Fine! Fine!) ♪

492
00:23:43,833 --> 00:23:45,875
♪ Singing with you! (Yay!) ♪

493
00:23:47,541 --> 00:23:49,625
[MAPLE]
The revenge concert is at hand!

494
00:23:49,708 --> 00:23:51,250
[YAIBA]
We have carried out our mission.

495
00:23:51,333 --> 00:23:53,750
Hence, we can only await
